"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-snoop-dogg-had-so-much-fun-carrying-olympic-torch-in-paris-and-fans-loved-it\", \"text\": \"The 2024 Paris Olympics officially kick off with theOpening Ceremony on Friday, which will feature a boat parade down the Seine before the Olympic cauldron is lit.  Speaking of being lit, Snoop Dogg had some fun with the Olympic torch hours before the Opening Ceremony, as he carried it for a bit in the streets of Paris, where he will be working throughout the Games for NBC.  The legendary rapper had too much fun doing this:  This is one time Snoop Dogg probably should not drop it like it's hot... \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0085\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00a5\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u00a5@Paris2024|#ParisOlympicspic.twitter.com/NWdVUvf6QK  Fans loved it:  This. The Olympic spirit!\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00a5\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00a5\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00a5https://t.co/Y3PUMBUn7s  Snoop\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s life/career arc is a movie, man.https://t.co/CRq0pmX9Eb  I wanna know how tempted he was to light a joint with that thing \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u00a3\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a4\\u00a3https://t.co/UatWuTGlh9  Love it!! \\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f@SnoopDogg#Paris2024https://t.co/08vaeaFtSX  1992 version of me would be stunned at thishttps://t.co/gnMSKBtmpF  All I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m saying is that it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a major L for the media if he doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t take it to light \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009csomething\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0089https://t.co/oHLMA14sKj  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Andy Nesbitt is the assistant managing editor of audience engagement at Sports Illustrated. He works closely with the Breaking and Trending News team to shape SI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s daily coverage across all sports. A 20-year veteran of the sports media business, he has worked for Fox Sports, For the Win, The 